Time Complexity:

Let n = number of operations

    Single traversal of operations → O(n)
    Final summation of stack → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    Stack stores up to n scores

Overall: O(n)


Approach:

1. Create a stack to store valid scores

2. Traverse each operation in array:

   - If operation is "C":
     → Remove last valid score (pop)

   - If operation is "D":
     → Push double of last score (2 * top)

   - If operation is "+":
     → Pop top element temporarily
     → Sum it with new top
     → Push back popped value
     → Push the computed sum

   - Else (number):
     → Convert string to integer
     → Push into stack

3. After processing all operations:
   - Sum all elements in stack

4. Return total sum






class Solution {
    public int calPoints(String[] operations) {
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();
        for(String ele: operations){
            if(ele.equals("C")){
                st.pop();
            }
            else if(ele.equals("D")){
                st.push(2*st.peek());
            }
            else if(ele.equals("+")){
                int popped = st.pop();
                int sum = popped + st.peek();
                st.push(popped);
                st.push(sum);
            }
            else{
                int num = Integer.parseInt(ele);
                st.push(num);
            }
        }
        int sum=0;
        while(st.size()!=0){
            sum+=st.pop();
        }
        return sum;
    }
}
